WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:07.400 --> 00:00:08.510
-Good morning, everyone.

00:00:08.510 --> 00:00:11.180
We're going to start this
morning with a blessing

00:00:11.180 --> 00:00:12.700
by Jonathan Perry.

00:00:33.020 --> 00:00:43.690
-[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:00:43.690 --> 00:00:47.080
Creator, we want to say thank
you for the great minds that

00:00:47.080 --> 00:00:50.410
have gathered here today
to share their knowledge

00:00:50.410 --> 00:00:53.110
and to help bring indigenous
issues and indigenous

00:00:53.110 --> 00:00:58.160
people to the forefront and
to a great future for all

00:00:58.160 --> 00:01:02.830
of our people, for opportunities
for sharing and opening

00:01:02.830 --> 00:01:06.900
our hearts and our minds, for
understanding and awareness

00:01:06.900 --> 00:01:08.790
and respect.

00:01:08.790 --> 00:01:11.810
We want to say thank you
to all of the families

00:01:11.810 --> 00:01:13.830
and all of the
people who sacrificed

00:01:13.830 --> 00:01:15.600
for us to be here today.

00:01:15.600 --> 00:01:18.560
We want to say thank
you to our ancestors,

00:01:18.560 --> 00:01:22.360
thank you to all the beings
that have helped us to achieve

00:01:22.360 --> 00:01:26.490
our goals, who sustain us,
nourish us, protect us,

00:01:26.490 --> 00:01:30.390
teach us, and care for
us every single day.

00:01:30.390 --> 00:01:32.650
We want to send our
blessings and prayers out

00:01:32.650 --> 00:01:35.780
to those who are
sick and who need

00:01:35.780 --> 00:01:38.040
our prayers or our
thoughts or our well

00:01:38.040 --> 00:01:40.710
wishes at this time, all
of those that were not

00:01:40.710 --> 00:01:46.170
able to attend this gathering or
were not able to travel with us

00:01:46.170 --> 00:01:50.530
or are not able to be
here in some fashion.

00:01:50.530 --> 00:01:53.450
I'd like to offer an
honor song for all of you

00:01:53.450 --> 00:01:55.650
and all of your
families at this time.

00:02:01.220 --> 00:05:22.970
[NATIVE AMERICAN SINGING]

00:05:22.970 --> 00:05:26.210
I want to say thank you for
coming to our territory.

00:05:26.210 --> 00:05:30.030
Thank you for joining
us in what is considered

00:05:30.030 --> 00:05:33.900
to be Wampanoag Nipmuc
Massachusetts territory,

00:05:33.900 --> 00:05:34.610
this area.

00:05:34.610 --> 00:05:36.600
This was, of course,
a thoroughfare

00:05:36.600 --> 00:05:40.830
for all of our people
both by the sea and land.

00:05:40.830 --> 00:05:44.110
And we have over
12,000 years, anyway,

00:05:44.110 --> 00:05:46.660
scientifically
proven success here.

00:05:46.660 --> 00:05:51.590
So we hope to revisit those
many, many years of success.

00:05:51.590 --> 00:05:54.930
And I think we'll do well.

00:05:54.930 --> 00:05:57.810
I just want to do
one more quick song,

00:05:57.810 --> 00:06:00.540
and I'd like to ask all
of you to help me with it.

00:06:00.540 --> 00:06:04.180
This is very specifically
a Wampanoag song.

00:06:04.180 --> 00:06:06.880
And normally we
would join hands,

00:06:06.880 --> 00:06:10.250
one hand to the back of the
shoulder on the heart side

00:06:10.250 --> 00:06:11.510
all the way around.

00:06:11.510 --> 00:06:14.750
But if you can, if
you can't, you can't.

00:06:14.750 --> 00:06:15.570
That's fine.

00:06:15.570 --> 00:06:18.170
But I need some
help singing this.

00:06:18.170 --> 00:06:18.820
It's very easy.

00:06:18.820 --> 00:06:20.280
So just join in as you can.

00:06:23.650 --> 00:07:29.300
