00:18:30.110 --> 00:18:32.810
Dan is the Director of the
Social Sciences Program

00:18:32.810 --> 00:18:36.440
here at the Radcliffe Institute,
the Allie S. Freed Professor

00:18:36.440 --> 00:18:38.480
of Government at
Harvard University,

00:18:38.480 --> 00:18:41.540
and a member of the Provost
Advisory Council on Native

00:18:41.540 --> 00:18:43.430
and Indigenous Issues.

00:18:43.430 --> 00:18:45.990
He is a political
scientist who specializes

00:18:45.990 --> 00:18:49.740
in public bureaucracies and
governmental regulation.

00:18:49.740 --> 00:18:54.290
He also studies diverse ways in
which individuals participate

00:18:54.290 --> 00:18:58.430
politically, what he calls
the performance of politics.

00:18:58.430 --> 00:19:00.890
Dan's research has
focused most intensively

00:19:00.890 --> 00:19:03.950
on petitioning among
groups often marginalized

00:19:03.950 --> 00:19:07.650
and disenfranchised throughout
much of American history,

00:19:07.650 --> 00:19:11.170
such as African Americans,
women, and Native Americans.

00:19:11.170 --> 00:19:13.440
So please join me
in thanking Dan

00:19:13.440 --> 00:19:16.570
for his hard work organizing
today's conference,

00:19:16.570 --> 00:19:18.770
and help me welcome
him to the podium.

00:19:18.770 --> 00:19:20.570
Dan.

00:19:20.570 --> 00:19:25.380
